                        "content": "The nurse is educating a client about medroxyprogesterone. The nurse would provide the client with which information about the medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nMedroxyprogesterone is given intramuscularly in the deltoid or gluteus maximus muscle. Injections needs to be administered every 12 weeks. Advantages of medroxyprogesterone include contraceptive effectiveness comparable to combined oral contraceptives and long-lasting effects. Additionally, injections are required only 4 times a year. Disadvantages are prolonged amenorrhea or uterine bleeding, increased risk of venous thrombosis and thromboembolism, and no protection against sexually transmitted infections.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, client education about medroxyprogesterone. Note that option 1 indicates administering the medication orally and option 2 indicates administration intramuscularly. These indicate opposite routes and that one of these options is likely the correct one. To select correctly, it is necessary to know that medroxyprogesterone is administered intramuscularly.",
